<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="2" pageNumber="47" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1901,2035]" pageId="2" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,340,1901,1926]" pageId="2" pageNumber="47">Description</emphasis>
. 
<typeStatus box="[359,463,1902,1926]" pageId="2" pageNumber="47">Holotype</typeStatus>
male, previously preserved in alcohol; specimen somewhat discolored by alcohol action. Body length 2.6 mm; wing length 3.9 mm. Frons shining black, wider than anterior ocellus width. Face slightly narrower than frons, approximately as wide as anterior ocellus width. Ocellar tubercle slightly protuberant with 
<number box="[209,223,2010,2034]" pageId="2" pageNumber="47" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of ocellar setae. Postcranium black, gray pruinose. Antenna yellow, flagellum with one flagellomere.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,971]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Proboscis yellow. Palpus yellowish. Thorax shining black, gray pruinose; postpronotal and postalar lobes slightly yellow. Thoracic setae: 
<number box="[421,435,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="2.0">2</number>
antepronotals; 
<number box="[611,653,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
minute proepisternals; 
<number box="[921,964,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7</number>
katatergitals; other setae as described for 
<taxonomicName box="[151,282,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbipennis">
<emphasis box="[151,282,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">limbipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group (diagnosed above). Legs shining yellow with mid and hind coxae, hind tibia and all tarsi slightly darker. Femora/tibiae setae slightly stronger: mid tibia (
<figureCitation box="[881,950,260,284]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[935,950,260,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) with 
<number box="[1027,1041,260,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
anterodorsal, 
<number box="[1205,1219,260,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
posterodorsal near middle, 
<number box="[242,284,295,319]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
ventral along distal half; hind femur (
<figureCitation box="[708,774,295,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[760,774,295,319]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) with 
<number box="[846,860,295,319]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
anteroventral at distal third; hind tibia (
<figureCitation box="[1304,1370,295,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[1356,1370,295,319]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) with 
<number box="[151,192,332,356]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
slender dorsal setae. 
<collectingCountry box="[440,496,332,356]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Hind</collectingCountry>
tarsomere 
<number box="[624,638,332,356]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
with one longer dorsal seta. Fore tarsus (
<figureCitation box="[1113,1179,332,356]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[1167,1179,332,356]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
) unicolorous with tarsomere 
<number box="[238,252,367,391]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
, swollen dorsally. Wing (
<figureCitation box="[539,606,367,391]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[591,606,367,391]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
) entirely hyaline with inconspicuous pterostigma. Cell dm truncate. Veins M 
<number box="[176,184,419,433]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
, M 
<number box="[223,231,419,433]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="2.0">2</number>
and A 
<number box="[307,315,419,433]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
evanescent. Halter white. Abdomen shining black, more gray pruinose on terminalia. Sternites 
<number box="[1394,1435,404,428]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
slightly yellow. Tergite 
<number box="[415,429,442,466]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[443,509,442,466]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[495,509,442,466]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
) with distal sinus. Epandrium (
<figureCitation box="[859,926,442,466]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[911,926,442,466]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
) with anterodorsal and posterodorsal lobes of same height with shallow sinus. Anterior cercus very large with internal sinus; posterior cercus somewhat short; median lobe membranous with long setae. Hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[802,872,514,538]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1687,1710]" captionTargetBox="[261,1326,338,1663]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[261,1327,338,1663]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Macrostomus inflatus, sp. nov. 1 – 7, paratype male. 1, fore leg; 2, mid leg; 3, hind leg; 4, wing; 5, tergite 8, dorsal view with right setae omitted; 6, terminalia, lateral view (epandrium electronic gray colored); 7, hypandrium and phallus, lateral view; 8 – 11, paratype female. 8, tergite 8, 10 and cercus, lateral view; 9, tergite 8, dorsal view; 10, sternite 8, ventral view; 11, genital fork, ventral view. Scales: 1 – 3 = 0.5 mm; 5 – 10 = 0.2 mm; 11 = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: AC, anterior cercus; AL, anterior lobe of epandrium; CE, cercus; EP, epandrium; MC, median cercus; PC, posterior cercus; PL, posterior lobe of epandrium; St, sternite; T, tergite." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281633/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[857,872,514,538]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
) with setae medially and apex somewhat simple. Ejaculatory apodeme with short dorsal lamella.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,971]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">
Female. Body length not measured; wing length 2.4 mm. Frons and face as in male. Fore tarsomere 
<number box="[1311,1325,586,610]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="1.0">1</number>
not swollen. 
<collectingCountry box="[199,255,623,647]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Hind</collectingCountry>
femur without anteroventral setae. 
<collectingCountry box="[652,708,623,647]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="48">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia with 
<number box="[828,842,623,647]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="3.0">3</number>
dorsal setae. Tergite 
<number box="[1079,1093,623,647]" pageId="3" pageNumber="48" value="8.0">8</number>
(
